-- Nordstrom December same-store sales fall 4 percent
-- 
-- Thu Jan 10, 2008 7:58am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/10/us-usa-retailsales-nordstrom-idUSWNAS611120080110

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Upscale department store chain Nordstrom Inc ( JWN.N ) said on Thursday that December sales at stores open at least a year fell 4 percent. 

 Analysts, on average, were expecting same-store sales to fall 4.1 percent, according to Reuters Estimates. The Seattle-based retailer said preliminary data indicated total sales for the five weeks ended January 5 fell 3.8 percent to $1.2 billion. (Reporting by  Aarthi Sivaraman ; editing by John Wallace)